    "After the bagasse is burned, the resulting ash is collected using large filters.",
    "Traditionally, this ash has been disposed of locally, which can lead to significant environmental challenges, especially in major sugar producing countries like Brazil, India, and Thailand.",
    "However, because of its high silica content, bagasse ash shows promise as a supplementary cementitious material in concrete production [1].",
